tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly decreased erythrocyte count. Hemoglobin and hematocrit are normal, suggesting no clinically significant anemia. Other red cell indices and platelet parameters are unremarkable. No acute hematological abnormality is evident; the isolated low erythrocyte count may be a benign variation but should be correlated clinically if symptoms are present.
